Grammy nominations: Michael Daugherty, Steve Mackey lead the classical music category
The classical music nominations at the 53rd Annual Grammy Awards feature a wide array of musicians and composers from around the world.
Leading the nominations are Michael Daugherty and his "Deus Ex Machina" for piano and orchestra, with five points, and Steve Mackey with his album "Dreamhouse", an eclectic orchestral work, with three points.
Among the nominees with ties to Southern California was Estonian composer Arvo Pärt and his Symphony No. 4 "Los Angeles", a work commissioned through the Los Angeles Philharmonic and debuted at Walt Disney Concert Hall in 2009.
L.A.-based composer Avner Dorman and his Mandolin Concerto are also up for an award.
The classical music nominations are divided into 13 categories, which include orchestral, operatic, choral and solo recordings.
