The classical album nomination was won by Bruckner and his Symphonies Nos. 3 and 4 with the Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra; Daugherty and his "Deus Ex Machina" and "Metropolis Symphony" with the Nashville Symphony Orchestra; Steven Mackey and his "Dreamhouse" with the Boston Modern Orchestra Project and Synergy Vocals; "Sacrificium - the Art of the Castrati" featuring various artists; and Verdi's "Requiem" with the Chicago Symphony Orchestra and Chorus.
In the opera category, nominated are Berg and "Lulu" by the Orchestra of the Royal Opera House; Adolf Hasse and "Marc Antonio e Cleopatra" by Ars Lyrica Houston; Kaija Saariaho and "L'Amour de Loin" by the Deutsches Symphonie-Orchester Berlin; Rodion Shchedrin and "The Enchanted Wanderer" by the Orchestra and Chorus of the Mariinsky Theatre; and Arthur Sullivan and "Ivanhoe" by the BBC National Orchestra of Wales.
Composers who are nominated for the Grammy for Contemporary Composition include Pärt for Symphony No. 4, Daugherty for "Deus Ex Machina", Hans Werner Henze for "Appassionatamente Plus", Magnus Lindberg for "Graffiti", and Shchedrin for "The Enchanted Wanderer".
Pärt's Symphony No. 4 premiered at Disney Hall in January 2009 at a performance recorded by the L.A. Philharmonic under the baton of Esa-Pekka Salonen.
The roughly 30-minute piece is called "Los Angeles" and is dedicated to former oil tycoon Mikhail Khodorkovsky, who is imprisoned in Russia.
Dorman and "Mandolin Concerto" was nominated for solo instrumental performance with orchestra.
The L.A. composer said he wrote the 15-minute piece specifically for mandolin player Avi Avitala, who was performing at a concert with the New York-based Metropolis Ensemble.
"I wrote it using Middle Eastern tones and many North African rhythms", Dorman said in a telephone interview.
Conductor Pierre Boulez, 85, received a nomination in the orchestral category for conducting the Chicago Symphony in a recording of Stravinsky's works.
Among the instrumental soloists who received nominations are pianists Nelson Freire and Marc-André Hamelin; organist Paul Jacobs; violist Julia Fischer; and harpist Sarah Schuster Ericsson.
This year, the only female soloists nominated were Anne Sofie Von Otter, Cecilia Bartoli, Lucia Duchon, Vivica Genaux and Measha Brueggergosman.
In the category of classical transition, soprano Jessye Norman was nominated for her recording of "Roots - My Life, My Song".
