Chief technology officer Steve Nevey says that five years ago it was possible to say that advances in vehicle research and development contributed 50% of the victory, and the rest was drivers' credit.
Today, that ratio has changed, and technology costs 85 percent of the success, while pilots contribute 15 percent.
Nevey acknowledges that Vettel or Webber will never be replaced by computer technology, since they are "unpredictable gladiators".
