Finally, in the last days of October, Merkel again came out with a clear position, demanding that the European Union treaties be reformed to allow for the rescue of a Member State while at the same time obliging private creditors to bear part of the costs.
This view was interpreted as anti-European, because it accelerated the Irish crisis and everything.
