The year 2013 will mark the birth of a new currency area, in which countries that break the rules will be severely punished and may be forced to declare deferrals, and the private sector will also have to bear some of the costs.
Germany suggests that we must take a rigid path of growth with increased savings and investment, moderate consumption, improved productivity and competitiveness, and capital reserves.
