The South Korean government is set to pass a law called "Pecival", which will ban teenagers from playing online games after midnight by blocking access to them, according to government officials.
A bill will be presented to Parliament in December to ask companies operating online games to block access to these games after midnight to people under the age of 16, said representatives of the Ministry of Culture and the Ministry of Family Affairs.
"Many children play these games all night and then have difficulty in school and are unable to lead a normal life during the day".
